Arguments

data

A data frame containing the observations. The other parameters specify the name of the columns
player0

A string with name of the column containing the players 0
player1

A string with name of the column containing the players 0
player0_score

A string with name of the column containing the scores of players 0
player1_score

A string with name of the column containing the scores of players 1
result_column

A string with name of the column containing the winners. 0 for player 0, 1 for player 1 and -1 for ties
model_type

'bradleyterry' (default), 'davidson' for ties
solve_ties

A string for the method of handling ties. 'random' for converting ties randomly, 'remove' for removing the tie occurrencess 'none' to ignore ties. The last requires a model to handle ties such as the davidson
win_score

A string that indicates if a 'higher' score is winner or if a 'lower' score is winner
prior_lambda_std

Positive value for the standard deviation of the normal prior if not uniform. Default is 2
chains

Number of chains passed to Stan sampling. Positive integer, default=4. For more information consult Stan
iter

Number of iterations passed to Stan sampling. Positive integer, default =2000. For more information consult Stan
warmup

Number of iteration for the warmup passed to Stan sampling. Positive integer, default 1000. For more information consult Stan
